        <p><strong>VMware</strong>, Inc. is a U.S. software company that provides cloud and virtualization software and services, and was the first to successfully virtualize the x86 architecture.</p>
        <p>Founded in 1998, VMware is based in Palo Alto, California. In 2004 it was acquired by and became a subsidiary of EMC Corporation, then on 14 August 2007, EMC sold 15% of the company in a New York Stock Exchange IPO. The company trades under the symbol VMW.</p>
        <p>VMware's desktop software runs on Microsoft {'Windows'|link_urls:'i'}, {'Linux'|link_urls:'i'}, and {'OS X'|link_urls:'i'}, while its enterprise software hypervisors for servers, VMware ESX and VMware ESXi, are bare-metal hypervisors that run directly on server hardware without requiring an additional underlying operating system.</p>
